cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use claude-conductor in academic or technical work, please cite it
  using the metadata below. The substrate is published as the discipline-as-
  code reference for AI-assisted multi-session software-engineering cohorts
  on Claude Code; cited work helps surface the discipline-thread + cohort-
  precedent vocabulary for future research + adoption.
type: software
title: claude-conductor
abstract: >-
  Discipline-as-code substrate for AI-assisted multi-session software-
  engineering cohorts on Claude Code. Provides primitives for inter-session
  coordination channels, NATO-phonetic identity claims, audit-verdict
  schemas, lineage envelopes, memory-attention scoring, canonical-JSON
  cross-runtime determinism, and reciprocation graph accounting. Designed
  for one operator running 2-4 Claude Code sessions in parallel with
  cohort-internal coordination + audit reciprocity discipline.
